text: Sebastes hubbsi is a species of fish in the rockfish family found in the Northwest Pacific. It grows to standard length. == Culinary use == In Korea, the fish is known as ureok () and used in fish soup. 서산 9미 우럭젓국.jpg|Ureok- jeot-guk (rockfish soup) == References == ==External links== * * Category:Sebastidae Category:Taxa named by Kiyomatsu Matsubara Category:Fish described in 1937 Category:Fish of the Pacific Ocean Category:Commercial fish
